definitions.definition: Personification of vast waters or the world ocean. He was the first-born of the Titans, son of Uranus and Gaia , the god Ωκεανός Ποταμός ( Ōkeanós Potamós , “ River Ocean ” ) that encircled the earth. With his sister-wife , Tethys , he fathered all rivers and the Oceanids .

main_definition: ( Greek mythology ) Personification of vast waters or the world ocean. He was the first-born of the Titans, son of Uranus and Gaia , the god Ωκεανός Ποταμός ( Ōkeanós Potamós , “ River Ocean ” ) that encircled the earth. With his sister-wife , Tethys , he fathered all rivers and the Oceanids .
